      pipe and filter commands

HEAD - This displays the head of the lines or data (when the number is mentioned)
FOR EG.
head -n 4 CSV_PROJECT.csv 


TAIL - This displays the head of the lines or data (when the number is mentioned) 
FOR EG.
tail -n 4 CSV_PROJECT.csv


CUT-This command can display any user specified column
FOR EG.
cut -d , -f 1 CSV_PROJECT.csv

SORT-It sorts the table according to the alphabets
FOR EG.
sort -d CSV_PROJECT.csv

WORD COUNT - It gives us a count with 3 blocks , i.e no. of lines , no. of words , no. of bytes.
FOR EG.
wc < CSV_PROJECT.csv


exercise

1. Display third column of filename.csv without printing the reader CGPA, also sort the same.
$cut -d , -f 3 CSA1.csv|grep -v cgpa|sort



2. Display only current time using date command.
$date +"%T"



3. Use unique with all possible options.
$uniq -c CSA1.csv



4. Print number of lines from ls-l command result.
$ls -l


     
5. Dispay USN from 7-14 along with other fields.
$tail -n 8 CSA1.csv 



6. Sort only name field from filename.csv.
$cut -d, -f 2 CSA1.csv|grep -v name|sort



7. Replace name with student name.
$cut -d, -f 2 CSA1.csv | head -n 1 |tr ["name"] ["student name"]
